					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>On the south wall, <hi rend="italic">kumuda</hi> portion of a ruined Īśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 10 = 981 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription records that Parāśaraṉ Tāyaṉ Sāttaṉ of Kiḷinallūr in order to provide food offerings alongwith vegetable side-dishes thrice on each day with four <hi rend="italic">nāḻi</hi> of rice, on the occasions of <hi rend="italic">Saṅkrānti</hi> and new moon days, to the god Yamadagnīśvaratt-āḻvār of Śeṟuvalūr in Oymā-nāḍu, donated one <hi rend="italic">cheṟuvu</hi> of land. The land was entrusted to the temple managers <hi rend="italic">(kōyil-uḍaiyār)</hi> who received the gift and agreed to carry out the charity.</p>						

						</summary>
